article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 74, Wiley 45
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Josh Alexander made four of five 3-pointers and scored 14 points to lead Stephen F. Austin past Wiley 74-45 on Saturday. Two of Alexander's 3-pointers came during a 15-2 run that gave the Lumberjacks (12-1) a 34-12 lead with 5:08 remaining in the first half. Terrell Jacob, with 11 points, was the only player in double figures for Wiley (12-3), which shot just 27 percent in the first half and 30 percent for the game. Benson Akpan had 10 points and eight rebounds off the bench for Stephen F. Austin. Scott Weaver had a game-high 10 rebounds.
